Here's the updated Privacy Policy for "Americamagujarati" for a social media channel focused on motivational content. I've replaced "GujjuWeds" with "Americamagujarati" and adjusted the context from a matrimonial service to a social media channel, while keeping the core legal structure.

Americamagujarati
Privacy Policy of Americamagujarati Social Media Channel

Privacy Policy
Effective date: June 6, 2025

Americamagujarati ("us", "we", or "our") operates the Americamagujarati social media channel and related content (the "Service").

This page informs you of our policies regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal data when you engage with our Service and the choices you have associated with that data.

We use your data to provide and improve the Service, which includes delivering motivational content and fostering community engagement. By engaging with the Service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy. Unless otherwise defined in this Privacy Policy, terms used in this Privacy Policy have the same meanings as in our Terms and Conditions.

Information Collection And Use
We collect several different types of information for various purposes to provide and improve our Service to you.

Types of Data Collected
Personal Data
While you engage with our Service, we may collect certain personally identifiable information that can be used to contact or identify you ("Personal Data"). This primarily occurs when you directly interact with us (e.g., through direct messages, comments, or explicit sign-ups for newsletters if offered). Personally identifiable information may include, but is not limited to:

Email address
First name and last name
Phone number (if voluntarily provided for communication)
Location data (e.g., city, state, if explicitly shared or inferred from public profile information)
Usage Data
We may also collect information that your browser sends whenever you visit our Service's platform pages (e.g., Facebook, Instagram, YouTube) or when you access the Service by or through a mobile device ("Usage Data"). This data is primarily collected and processed by the social media platforms themselves, and we receive aggregated, anonymized insights from them.

This Usage Data may include information such as your computer's Internet Protocol address (e.g. IP address), browser type, browser version, the pages of our Service that you visit on the platform, the time and date of your visit, the time spent on those pages, unique device identifiers and other diagnostic data.

When you access the Service by or through a mobile device, this Usage Data may include information such as the type of mobile device you use, your mobile device unique ID, the IP address of your mobile device, your mobile operating system, the type of mobile Internet browser you use, unique device identifiers and other diagnostic data.

Tracking & Cookies Data
We, through the underlying social media platforms, may use cookies and similar tracking technologies to track activity on our Service and hold certain information. These technologies are managed by the respective social media platforms (e.g., Facebook, Google, YouTube).

Cookies are files with small amounts of data which may include an anonymous unique identifier. Cookies are sent to your browser from a website and stored on your device. Tracking technologies also used are beacons, tags, and scripts to collect and track information and to improve and analyze our Service.

You can instruct your browser or your social media platform settings to refuse all cookies or to indicate when a cookie is being sent. However, if you do not accept cookies, you may not be able to use some portions of our Service or the underlying platforms.

Examples of Cookies used by social media platforms we operate on:

Session Cookies. Used to operate the Service and maintain user sessions.
Preference Cookies. Used to remember user preferences and various settings.
Security Cookies. Used for security purposes.
Use of Data
Americamagujarati uses the collected data for various purposes:

To provide and maintain the Service (e.g., deliver content)
To notify you about changes or new content on our Service
To allow you to participate in interactive features of our Service (e.g., comments, polls) when you choose to do so
To provide analysis or valuable information so that we can improve the motivational content and engagement
To monitor the usage of the Service (through platform insights)
To detect, prevent and address technical issues or misuse
Transfer Of Data
Your information, including Personal Data, may be transferred to — and maintained on — computers located outside of your state, province, country or other governmental jurisdiction where the data protection laws may differ than those from your jurisdiction. This includes data processed by the social media platforms themselves.

If you are located outside United States and choose to provide information to us, please note that we transfer the data, including Personal Data, to United States and process it there.

Your engagement with this Service and submission of such information represents your agreement to that transfer.

Americamagujarati will take all steps reasonably necessary to ensure that your data is treated securely and in accordance with this Privacy Policy and no transfer of your Personal Data will take place to an organization or a country unless there are adequate controls in place including the security of your data and other personal information.

Disclosure Of Data
Legal Requirements
Americamagujarati may disclose your Personal Data in the good faith belief that such action is necessary to:

To comply with a legal obligation
To protect and defend the rights or property of Americamagujarati
To prevent or investigate possible wrongdoing in connection with the Service
To protect the personal safety of users of the Service or the public
To protect against legal liability
Security Of Data
The security of your data is important to us, but remember that no method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your Personal Data, we cannot guarantee its absolute security. Data stored by the social media platforms is subject to their security measures.

Service Providers
We may employ third party companies and individuals to facilitate our Service ("Service Providers"), to provide the Service on our behalf, to perform Service-related services or to assist us in analyzing how our Service is used. These primarily include the social media platforms themselves (e.g., Meta for Facebook/Instagram, Google for YouTube).

These third parties have access to your Personal Data only to perform these tasks on our behalf and are obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose beyond what is required for their platform functionality.

Analytics
We use third-party Service Providers to monitor and analyze the use of our Service, primarily through the tools provided by the social media platforms.

Google Analytics
Google Analytics is a web analytics service offered by Google that tracks and reports website traffic. Google uses the data collected to track and monitor the use of our Service. This data is shared with other Google services. Google may use the collected data to contextualize and personalize the ads of its own advertising network.
For more information on the privacy practices of Google, please visit the Google Privacy & Terms web page: https://policies.google.com/privacy?hl=en

Firebase
Firebase is an analytics service provided by Google Inc.
You may opt-out of certain Firebase features through your mobile device settings, such as your device advertising settings or by following the instructions provided by Google in their Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy?hl=en
We also encourage you to review Google's policy for safeguarding your data: https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/6004245. For more information on what type of information Firebase collects, please visit the Google Privacy & Terms web page: https://policies.google.com/privacy?hl=en

Links To Other Sites
Our Service may contain links to other sites that are not operated by us. If you click on a third party link, you will be directed to that third party's site. We strongly advise you to review the Privacy Policy of every site you visit.

We have no control over and assume no responsibility for the content, privacy policies or practices of any third party sites or services.

Children's Privacy
Our Service does not address anyone under the age of 18 ("Children").

We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from anyone under the age of 18. If you are a parent or guardian and you are aware that your Children has provided us with Personal Data, please contact us. If we become aware that we have collected Personal Data from children without verification of parental consent, we take steps to remove that information from our servers.

Changes To This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.

We will let you know via email (if we have your email contact through other means) and/or a prominent notice on our Service's platforms, prior to the change becoming effective and update the "effective date" at the top of this Privacy Policy.

You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Changes to this Privacy Policy are effective when they are posted on this page.

Contact Us
